            <thetext>I have fixed this in the mobile framework with a
&quot;exclude&quot; CSS class.

.exclude {
  display:none !important;
}

The exclude method adds the class and the show method removes it. This has the
following advantages: Even when someone changes the display value in the
framework JS code (e.g. in the atom widget orientation) with an inline style,
the display:none !important will win.</thetext>
